      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Those feelings of nihilism are incredibly heavy, especially when confronting the vast emptiness of the universe, yet finding meaning doesn't always require a grand purpose—sometimes it lies simply in the depth of shared human experiences. While death is an end, the connections we forge with others and the joy we feel in a sunrise create a profound intensity that can feel worth enduring even for a flash of light. If despair feels overwhelming, please reach out to someone you trust or a mental health support line, because feeling hopeless is distressing even if it often doesn't hurt to feel hopeless.",
